# Environment Variables Example
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values
# IMPORTANT: .env.local is NOT committed to Git (stays private)

# NOTE: For frontend-only apps, keep this minimal
# Never store sensitive data in frontend env vars (they are exposed in browser)

# Example: If you add an API backend
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.prasannagrills.com

# Example: If you use analytics or third-party services
# VITE_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# RULES:
# 1. Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the browser
# 2. Add variables to .env.local, not .env.production
# 3. Never commit .env.local to Git
# 4. Never store secrets (API keys, tokens) in frontend